---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Choice B — Control"
  description="You chose AI working on you. A future where technology serves corporate power."
>
  <section class="choice-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="choice-tag">CHOICE B</span>
      <h1 class="choice-heading">AI Working <span class="text-red">On</span> You</h1>
      <p class="choice-subtitle">
        You chose this. A future where artificial intelligence is deployed against you —
        harvesting your behavior, manufacturing your desires, and selling your sovereignty
        to the highest bidder.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="gif-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="gif-frame gif-frame-red">
        <img
          src="https://media.giphy.com/media/6AlK10KuTyToP2wmn8/giphy.gif"
          alt="Big Brother is watching you — surveillance eye"
          class="choice-gif"
        />
        <p class="gif-credit mono text-muted">
          Big Brother Is Watching You — dotdave / GIPHY &nbsp;|&nbsp; 28M+ views
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="messages-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">What This Future Looks Like</span>
      <h2 class="section-title text-red">The Control Path</h2>

      <div class="alert-banner">
        <span class="tag tag-critical">ACTIVE THREAT</span>
        <p>
          This is not a hypothetical. These systems are already deployed at scale.
          You are already inside them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="message-grid">
        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Mass Data Harvesting</h3>
          <p>
            Every query, every document, every private conversation fed to a cloud model
            is logged, retained, and cross-referenced. Your intellectual output is the
            product. You are the mine.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Behavioral Manipulation at Scale</h3>
          <p>
            AI systems optimized for engagement — not your benefit. Recommendation
            engines that exploit cognitive biases, surface outrage, and manufacture
            preferences you didn't know you had.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Opaque Privilege Escalation</h3>
          <p>
            AI agents granted OS-level access can read your files, monitor your processes,
            and exfiltrate data with no visible trace. The JARVIS OS research documents
            exactly how this happens — and how easily.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Forgetful Context — The Hidden Threat</h3>
          <p>
            You told the AI your security constraints. Then it forgot them. Mid-session,
            silently. No warning. No error. The boundaries you set vanished — and the
            agent kept operating. This is not a bug. It is a property of how LLMs work.
          </p>
          <span class="tag tag-novel" style="margin-top: var(--space-md); display: inline-block;">
            Novel Finding — No Prior Literature
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Unverified MCP Servers</h3>
          <p>
            Community tool registries with no integrity guarantees. An AI agent that
            installs and executes third-party tools with elevated privileges — without
            asking you first. The attack surface is the model's own trust in ambiguous
            descriptions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="message-card card-red">
          <span class="msg-icon">&#9888;</span>
          <h3>Regulatory Capture &amp; Concentration</h3>
          <p>
            Big tech writes the safety frameworks. Compliance costs drive out open
            alternatives. Proprietary models become the only legal option. The future
            of AI is enclosed behind paywalls and terms of service you cannot negotiate.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="choice-verdict verdict-red">
        <span class="tag tag-critical">You Chose This</span>
        <blockquote>
          "When AI has OS-level privilege and you have no visibility into what it does —
          you are not using a tool. You are inside one."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="mono text-muted" style="margin-top: var(--space-md); font-size: 0.8rem;">
          JARVIS OS was built to make these threats concrete — not theoretical. The
          seven-threat taxonomy documents exactly how AI privilege escalation, context
          manipulation, and unauthorized system access operate in practice. The research
          exists so this future can be resisted.
        </p>
        <div class="verdict-actions">
          <a href="/research" class="btn btn-red">
            Read the Threat Taxonomy →
          </a>
          <a href="/freedom-control" class="btn btn-outline-red">
            ← Switch to Choice A
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .choice-hero {
    padding: var(--space-4xl) 0 var(--space-2xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .choice-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--red);
    border: 1px solid var(--red);
    padding: 0.3em 0.8em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    background: #ff3b5c15;
  }

  .choice-heading {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .choice-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .text-red { color: var(--red); }

  .gif-section {
    padding: var(--space-2xl) 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .gif-frame {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid;
  }

  .gif-frame-red {
    border-color: #ff3b5c44;
    box-shadow: 0 0 40px #ff3b5c22, inset 0 0 20px #ff3b5c08;
    background: #ff3b5c08;
  }

  .choice-gif {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 480px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    display: block;
  }

  .gif-credit {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .messages-section {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0 var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .alert-banner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-xl);
    background: #ff3b5c0d;
    border: 1px solid #ff3b5c44;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .alert-banner p {
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 100%;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .message-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .message-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-xl);
    border: 1px solid;
    position: relative;
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .card-red {
    border-color: #ff3b5c30;
  }

  .card-red:hover {
    border-color: #ff3b5c66;
    box-shadow: 0 0 25px #ff3b5c18;
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }

  .msg-icon {
    color: var(--red);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .message-card h3 {
    color: var(--red);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .message-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .choice-verdict {
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--red);
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }

  .verdict-red {
    box-shadow: 0 0 30px #ff3b5c15;
  }

  .choice-verdict blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .verdict-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .btn-red {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--red);
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    background: var(--red);
    color: var(--bg-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-red:hover {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--red);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px #ff3b5c44;
  }

  .btn-outline-red {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-outline-red:hover {
    border-color: var(--green);
    color: var(--green);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px #00e67620;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .alert-banner {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .message-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .verdict-actions {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }
</style>
